</h2>
<p>
    Perched in Central Oregon’s high desert, <strong>Bend</strong> offers anglers a smorgasbord of trout waters—from cool spring-fed streams and blue-ribbon tailwaters to clear alpine lakes. Within an hour’s drive, you can find <strong>wild redband trout in the Crooked River</strong>, <strong>giant rainbows at Crane Prairie</strong>, or <strong>brookies and browns in crystal-clear mountain lakes</strong>. For families and fly-fishers alike, Bend is a trout paradise.
</p>
