<h2>
    <strong>Top Rivers for Trout from Bend</strong>
</h2>
<h3>
    <strong>Crooked River</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    A tailwater fantasy for wild redband trout. Guided trips boast consistent success with small nymphs and indicators below Bowman Dam
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Deschutes River (Upper &amp; Lower)</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Home to redbands, browns, and whitefish. Fly angling thrives year-round; fall produces trophy browns
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Metolius River</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Spring-fed clarity and native rainbows—fly-only above Bridge 99, artificial-lure allowed below
</p>
<h2>
    <strong>Best Lakes Near Bend</strong>
</h2>
<h3>
    <strong>Crane Prairie Reservoir</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Famous trophy rainbows and big browns in snaggy water. Fly or spin works; reservoir averages 15‑20 ft depth .
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>East, Paulina &amp; Hosmer Lakes</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    High-country trout hubs: East (rainbows, kokanee), Paulina (browns, kokanee), and fly-fishing–only Hosmer (brook &amp; rainbow) <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.bestfishinginamerica.com/OR-best-fishing-in-central-zone-south-lakes.html?utm_source=chatgpt.com">Best Fishing in America</a>.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Sparks &amp; Devil’s Lakes</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Devil’s: family-friendly trout &amp; brookies via shoreline; Sparks: scenic fly-fishing hotspot
</p>
<h2>
    <strong>Bank, Wading vs. Boat Access</strong>
</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Bank/Wading</strong>: Ideal on rivers and small lakes like Devil’s, Sparks, Crooked.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Boat Access</strong>: Needed at Crane Prairie and East/Paulina; float tubes welcome at Hosmer
    </li>
</ul>
<h2>
    <strong>Techniques &amp; Gear for Success</strong>
</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Fly Fishing</strong>: 4–6 wt rods with nymphs (Pheasant Tails, Zebra Midges), dries (Elk Hair Caddis, PMDs) .
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Spinning Gear</strong>: Small spoons, Rooster Tails, inline spinners on reservoirs.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Bait Fishing</strong>: PowerBait and salmon eggs in Kid-access lakes.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Seasonal Tweak</strong>: Midge rigs below the dam; streamers on muddy banks in fall.
    </li>
</ul>
